notificationTaskList.title = Submit a notification
notificationTaskList.heading = Submit a notification
notificationTaskList.paragraph1 = Submit a notification for each Senior Accounting Officer (SAO) in your group. Each notification must include the SAO’s name and all the entities they were responsible for during the financial year.
notificationTaskList.provideSaoDetailsLinkText = Provide the SAO’s details
notificationTaskList.uploadNotificationLinkText = Upload the submission template
notificationTaskList.submitNotificationLinkText = Submit the notification
notificationTaskList.homepageText = Go back to the homepage

notificationTaskList.row.status.cannotStartYet = Cannot start yet
notificationTaskList.row.status.completed = Completed
notificationTaskList.row.status.notStarted = Not started

template.guidance.title = Notification and certificate submission template guidance
template.guidance.heading = Submission template guidance

template.guidance.paragraph1 = This is a step by step guide on how to submit a notification and certificate using the submission template.

template.guidance.subheading1 = Step 1: Download and complete a submission template
template.guidance.subheading1.downloadTemplateLinkText = Download the submission template.
template.guidance.subheading1.paragraph1 = Fill in all required fields for each company in your group. Each row should represent one company the SAO was responsible for in the previous financial year.
template.guidance.subheading1.paragraph2 = Do not change the layout or structure of the template, if you do, the upload will fail.
template.guidance.subheading1.paragraph3 = Use the guidance in row 3 under each column heading to help you enter the information correctly.

template.guidance.subheading2 = Step 2: Upload your template
template.guidance.subheading2.paragraph1 = When you’ve completed your template:
template.guidance.subheading2.list1.item1 = Save it as a CSV (comma delimited) file.
template.guidance.subheading2.list1.item2 = Upload it to the service.
template.guidance.subheading2.list1.item3 = Check that all details are correct.
template.guidance.subheading2.list1.item4 = Submit the file to complete your notification and certificate.
template.guidance.subheading2.inset.text = If you only completed the notification section, you’ll need to re-upload the same template later when you’re ready to complete your certificate.

template.guidance.subheading3 = Step 3: Check the information is correct
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph1 = Before you submit your certificate, you can check the information you uploaded is correct.
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph2WithLink = If the information is not correct, <a class="govuk-link" href="{0}">upload an updated submission template</a> before continuing.
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph3 = If there are any errors when you try to upload the template (for example, missing or invalid data), you’ll be shown a list of what to fix.
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph4 = You can:
template.guidance.subheading3.list1.item1 = correct the errors in your Excel file
template.guidance.subheading3.list1.item2 = save again as a CSV
template.guidance.subheading3.list1.item3 = upload the file again
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph5 = Guidance is also included in the template to help you complete each field correctly.
template.guidance.subheading3.paragraph6 = Keep a copy of your uploaded CSV files for your records.

template.guidance.subheading4 = Step 4: Make your submission
template.guidance.subheading4.paragraph1 = When you upload your completed template:
template.guidance.subheading4.list1.item1 = notification details will be used to complete your notification
template.guidance.subheading4.list1.item2 = certificate details will be used to complete your certificate

template.guidance.subheading5 = Complete both notification and certificate at the same time
template.guidance.subheading5.list1.item1 = Start your submission by uploading the template and submitting your notification.
template.guidance.subheading5.list1.item2 = After notification is submitted, complete the certificate journey to finish your submission.

template.guidance.subheading6 = Complete certificate at a different time.
template.guidance.subheading6.list1.item1 = Upload your template again with certificate information filled out.
template.guidance.subheading6.list1.item2 = Complete the certificate journey and sign the declaration.

notificationUploadForm.title = Upload a submission template for your notification
notificationUploadForm.heading = Upload a submission template
notificationUploadForm.caption = Submit a notification
notificationUploadForm.paragraph1 = The template must be uploaded in CSV format. If you already have the template saved in a different format (such as .xls or .xlsx), you must save it again as a CSV file.
notificationUploadForm.paragraph2 = Read guidance on how to complete the submission template (opens in new tab)
notificationUploadForm.inset.text = If your group has more than one SAO, you must submit a separate notification for each SAO. After you complete one submission, you can start another.
notificationUploadForm.upload.label = Upload a file
notificationUploadForm.upload.error.quarantine = The selected file contains a virus
notificationUploadForm.upload.error.rejected = The selected file must be a CSV
notificationUploadForm.upload.error.unknown = The selected file could not be uploaded – try again

notificationGuidance.title = Submit a notification
notificationGuidance.heading = Submit a notification
notificationGuidance.paragraph1 = Tell HMRC who was responsible for your company’s tax accounting arrangement during the previous financial year.
notificationGuidance.paragraph2 = Each notification must include:
notificationGuidance.list1.item1 = the name and contact details of each person who acted as the Senior Accounting Officer 
notificationGuidance.list1.item2 = the accounting period they were responsible during the previous financial year 
notificationGuidance.list1.item3 = the name, Unique Taxpayer Reference (UTR) and Company Registration Number (CRN) of every company the SAO was responsible for, if your company is part of a group 
notificationGuidance.paragraph3 = Only one notification can be submitted per financial year. If more than one person acted as SAO, include all of them in the same notification.
notificationGuidance.inset.text = You can only submit the notification after the financial year has ended. The deadline is 6 months after the end of the financial year for public limited companies and 9 months after for other companies.

notificationAdditionalInformation.caption = Submit a notification
notificationAdditionalInformation.title = Notification details
notificationAdditionalInformation.heading = Additional information
notificationAdditionalInformation.paragraph1 = Tell us if there’s anything we should know about your notification or the companies listed.
notificationAdditionalInformation.paragraph2 = This could include:
notificationAdditionalInformation.list1.item1 = a company’s status changing, such as becoming dormant or going into liquidation
notificationAdditionalInformation.list1.item2 = anything else relevant to the companies listed
notificationAdditionalInformation.label = Provide information about your notification
notificationAdditionalInformation.checkYourAnswersLabel = Additional information
notificationAdditionalInformation.error.required = Enter information about your notification or skip
notificationAdditionalInformation.error.length = NotificationAdditionalInformation must be 5000 characters or less
notificationAdditionalInformation.change.hidden =  the additional information supplied for the notification (Financial year end {0})
notificationAdditionalInformation.empty = Not provided

notificationCheckYourAnswers.title = Check your answers
notificationCheckYourAnswers.heading = Check your answers
notificationCheckYourAnswers.caption = Submit a notification
notificationCheckYourAnswers.card.title = Financial year end {0}

submitNotification.title = Confirm notification and submit
submitNotification.heading = Confirm and submit a notification
submitNotification.caption = Submit a notification
submitNotification.paragraph1 = You confirm that this is an official notification to HMRC in relation to the Senior Accounting Officer requirement in accordance with Schedule 46 of the Finance Act 2009.
submitNotification.paragraph2 = By sending the notification you agree that the information you have given is complete and correct. If you deliberately give wrong or incomplete information, or do not report changes, the company may have to pay a penalty of £5,000.
submitNotification.inset.text = If you later realise you’ve submitted incorrect information, contact your Customer Compliance Manager if you have one, or the Customer Engagement Team for support.
submitNotification.button = Confirm and submit

notificationConfirmation.title = Submit a notification - Notification submitted
notificationConfirmation.heading = Notification submitted
notificationConfirmation.reference.text = Your reference number
notificationConfirmation.paragraph1 = We’ve sent a confirmation email to all the contacts you gave during registration.
notificationConfirmation.paragraph2 = To keep a record of your submission, you can:
notificationConfirmation.paragraph3 = Your notification has been received by HMRC. A member of compliance staff may contact you if they need more information.
notificationConfirmation.paragraph4 = You can now submit a Senior Accounting Officer certificate or another notification on behalf of another SAO in your group on your account homepage.
notificationConfirmation.downloadPdf = Download a PDF
notificationConfirmation.printPage = Print this page
notificationConfirmation.list1.item1 = - save a copy of all the answers you submitted now. You may not be able to download a PDF if you leave this page
notificationConfirmation.list1.item2 = - print a paper copy of this confirmation page
notificationConfirmation.subheading = What happens next

submitCertificateStart.title = Submit a certificate
submitCertificateStart.heading = Submit a certificate
submitCertificateStart.caption = Submit a certificate
submitCertificateStart.paragraph1 = The company details and tax regimes you provided in the uploaded template will be used to prepare your certificate.
submitCertificateStart.paragraph2WithLink = If you need to update company details or tax information, you can <a {0}>upload another submission template</a> again before continuing.
submitCertificateStart.paragraph3 = If you have qualified companies:
submitCertificateStart.list1.item1 = You’ll need to review the list of companies identified as qualified and confirm that is it correct before continuing.
submitCertificateStart.list1.item2 = You’ll also need to confirm the number of qualified company in the certificate statement before submitting the certificate.

