certificateWhoIsSubmitting.title = Who is submitting the certificate?
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.caption = Submit a certificate
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.heading = Who is submitting the certificate?
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.paragraph1 = HMRC need to know if the certificate will be submitted by the SAO or by someone authorised to act on their behalf. This allows us to show the correct declaration for the person submitting it.
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.paragraph2 = We rely on the information provided to be accurate. The SAO is responsible for reviewing and approving the information before it is submitted, and for authorising someone to submit it on their behalf if they are not submitting it themselves.
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.sao = I am the SAO
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.standIn = I am authorised to submit on behalf of the SAO
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.checkYourAnswersLabel = certificateWhoIsSubmitting
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.error.required = Select I am the SAO if you are the SAO submitting the certificate
certificateWhoIsSubmitting.change.hidden = CertificateWhoIsSubmitting

certificateCheckYourAnswers.title = certificateCheckYourAnswers
certificateCheckYourAnswers.heading = certificateCheckYourAnswers

certificateConfirmation.title = certificateConfirmation
certificateConfirmation.heading = certificateConfirmation

certificateDeclarationSao.title = Confirm the certificate
certificateDeclarationSao.heading = Confirm the certificate
certificateDeclarationSao.label = I am the Senior Accounting Officer with the authority to submit this certificate:
certificateDeclarationSao.hint = Insert full name
certificateDeclarationSao.subheading = Declaration
certificateDeclarationSao.caption = Submit a certificate
certificateDeclarationSao.paragraph1 = As the SAO it is your responsibility to make sure you have reviewed and approved everything before you submit.
certificateDeclarationSao.paragraph2 = By submitting this certificate, you confirm that:
certificateDeclarationSao.paragraph3 = if you deliberately give wrong or incomplete information, or do not report changes, the SAO may have to pay a penalty of £5,000.
certificateDeclarationSao.list1.item1 = the information is complete and correct
certificateDeclarationSao.list1.item2 = you are the SAO submitting this certificate
certificateDeclarationSao.inset.text = If you realise the information you submitted is incorrect, contact HMRC using your usual compliance contact or existing support channels.
certificateDeclarationSao.button = Confirm
certificateDeclarationSao.checkYourAnswersLabel = certificateDeclarationSao
certificateDeclarationSao.error.required = Enter the name of the Senior Accounting Officer who is authorised to submit the certificate
certificateDeclarationSao.error.length = The authorised person name you enter must be 105 characters or less
certificateDeclarationSao.change.hidden = CertificateDeclarationSao

